<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-A1843CF6-5762-4FEC-9CF3-EF86B7960A0F" version="3" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-A1843CF6-5762-4FEC-9CF3-EF86B7960A0F" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">11 How to remove the <ph varref="controller" class="- topic/ph ">Windows controller</ph> (11pba04)</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-0E3E2CA2-5349-4FAF-80F5-347AA9765351"><p class="- topic/p ">This document describes how to remove the <ph class="- topic/ph " varref="controller">Windows controller</ph> from the windows system. 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-610BC863-F7A5-476F-BDAB-783E9B196A7B" type="important"><p class="- topic/p "> NEVER combine multiple of the actions below at once: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">(Clean) installation of the system software 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Replace the Windows controller 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Replace DRC PBA (21PBA04) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Install used Printheads 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "> After each change of a topic listed above a system start-up/reboot must be executed to safeguard settings persistence. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Ignoring this, will result in the need for a restore action and involvement of Service and Support CPP is required. 
</p></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Dis-assembly</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-F8EE43B1-36AF-4F86-8810-3B686A03AF19" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_53184B16D403439F881DA2AB90C20E0F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Power off the system</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">On the operator panel, tap on the [System] icon on the right. Tap on [Power management]. Tap on [Power off]. The system shuts down. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Switch off the power supply</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After the system has shut down, loosen the 2 screws of the media output lower cover. Lift and remove the cover. Switch the power switch to the 'off' position. 
</p></li><li id="LI_719C03885B0C4EF3B8A90E91E1F7C293" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the printing system from mains. 
</p></li><li id="LI_C4E6554D4D1E4A458BEF9A08F728017A" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the chiller to get access to the controller. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref scope="local" format="dita" keyref="06DISA003" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?></xref> 
</p></li></ol><note type="important" id="GUID-C5DDA43B-326C-49A5-A87F-C6D341BD4C04" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the optical connection from the<ph varref="Econtroller" class="- topic/ph ">Embedded controller</ph> and put the end caps on the cable. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If anything goes wrong this cable gets damaged easily and it takes a lot of work to replace. 
</p></note></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_A9A4A5B37FE248AA9A057818C3F02FE3" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_9BC0C9602C354D39AC24A2A40B51D1A0" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20. 
</p></li></ul><note id="GUID-8F466F1D-1264-4978-A9B0-E40AC3E891B3" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">If the controller is replaced by a 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">new controller</b>, you need the following: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">new CMstick 
</b>(for the licenses). See : 
<xref keyref="GENINSTALLLICENSE001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-83541379-2C72-4191-948E-292B66F16EE2.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>How to request a license</xref> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Installation of the system software. see: 
<xref keyref="InstEmpty" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-529FDEAE-661F-43DF-B38C-73FFFD30D55B.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>11 How to do a system software installation on an empty disk</xref> 
</p></li></ul></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-1C6A5506-8461-4BFD-8B7C-FB47C7EF289A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0144023C-DAB7-48CC-A096-0388A5247AF4-low.png" id="IMAGE_11C42836423349909C7CB2DFC5595CFA" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0144023C-DAB7-48CC-A096-0388A5247AF4-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_1055F1FE61CD46A59B0D1129A54F5385" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_96623E8E8BDE460FAA0916E3550197B5" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Disconnect all connector on the right and left hand side. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Take note of where each connector was connected. Especially the USB connections. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_E5A430428183485AAB5BD6A2D29B26B8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6C40CBE0-315F-4E2E-9D9A-E4EC12CEE0D2-low.png" id="IMAGE_9C6C1545A3904AB8B559C08B8E78D590" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6C40CBE0-315F-4E2E-9D9A-E4EC12CEE0D2-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_21D8CA00B54D4A02A2F570CAEF222BE4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-CACDDE80-22F6-45A3-954C-1D1B2AA79890-low.png" id="IMAGE_FE1BCFA450C8473BBC5A311AF960CFF6" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CACDDE80-22F6-45A3-954C-1D1B2AA79890-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_1F1ECD9121774C0EB8487846FFB670F4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-337D81F4-C5FE-4BF5-A172-3F4FF112F627-low.png" id="IMAGE_F5915EA6CC1C4C11B049D123181E176D" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-337D81F4-C5FE-4BF5-A172-3F4FF112F627-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the power connection at the top. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_9DE77502637247CA953EDDA9CCC3EF8E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C31CDABC-580F-4299-951A-2BD7267021F5-low.png" id="IMAGE_A95672BC768C4F7DA30E6C756C410BD1" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C31CDABC-580F-4299-951A-2BD7267021F5-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Loosen</b> the left hand screw at the top. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Remove</b> the right hand screw at the top. 
</p><note id="GUID-21B4D760-5C92-4081-A34A-0C1984BD1D24" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Hold the controller while you do this so does not fall down. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_C55BABF75CBE48B7BB9B18C438BE805E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-71DFA174-0ABB-472F-ADBD-632335FDE010-low.png" id="IMAGE_3CD0D46CE3584076B586F96D532963F2" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-71DFA174-0ABB-472F-ADBD-632335FDE010-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_764DF02228DA4D48B4C8B2166E96A4D7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A11D204C-2573-4D8B-8825-4A4F86F5472C-low.png" id="IMAGE_BB8CB89F7F984EF5818B04911663F1AE" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A11D204C-2573-4D8B-8825-4A4F86F5472C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Lift and remove the controller. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_AB6EF30C67304CA48FC18BB9EB4746A1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0144023C-DAB7-48CC-A096-0388A5247AF4-low.png" id="IMAGE_4D0C94EEBE9D45F09DDA0FDA9D8F659D" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0144023C-DAB7-48CC-A096-0388A5247AF4-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_F623CDDFFE5D45DAA455F71000A7943F" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Install in reverse order. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In case of doubt see : 
<xref keyref="11COMP03" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-10C63E34-D014-4901-BD68-841AA6DE9A56.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>11 The connections on the Windows controller</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the ON/OFF switch of the <ph varref="controller" class="- topic/ph ">Windows controller</ph> is in the ON position. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reconnect the optical connection on the <ph varref="Econtroller" class="- topic/ph ">Embedded controller</ph> and put the end caps away. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><note id="GUID-B85C6C50-CE3D-421E-A96D-DF8A84298DA2" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">If the controller is replaced by a 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">new controller</b>, you need the following: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">new CMstick 
</b>(for the licenses). See : 
<xref keyref="GENINSTALLLICENSE001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-83541379-2C72-4191-948E-292B66F16EE2.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>How to request a license</xref> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Installation of the system software. see: 
<xref keyref="InstEmpty" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-529FDEAE-661F-43DF-B38C-73FFFD30D55B.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>11 How to do a system software installation on an empty disk</xref> 
</p></li></ul></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-39F03561-726E-48AE-8499-199AA586A300.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>